    "system_description": "Russian case + aspect disambiguation. Six grammatical cases (nominative, accusative, genitive, dative, instrumental, prepositional) with gender and number agreement encode argument roles with near-full disambiguation even under free word order. The perfective/imperfective aspect pair is an independent compression axis: it encodes whether the action is bounded (completed DCP event) or unbounded (open process). Negation in Russian triggers genitive case on the object (Я не вижу книги vs Я вижу книгу) — the negation itself is a case-selection trigger.",
